  <original-body>Not specifying a database when connecting to a mysql server is allowed.  Doing so allows one to refer to tables in different databases on the same server in the same query, which is often useful.  Support for this is actually already present in vendor/mysql.rb, but is specifically disabled in connection_adapters/mysql_adapter.rb (if no :database argument is specified to establish_connection, an exception is thrown).  Removing this check allows cross-db joins.</original-body>
